-- Half of Australia's Wheat Crop May Be Downgraded After Rainfall, NAB Says
-- B y   W e n d y   P u g h
-- 2010-12-21T00:14:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-21/half-of-australia-s-wheat-crop-may-be-downgraded-after-rainfall-nab-says.html
National Australia Bank Ltd.
estimated that “roughly half” Australia’s 24 million metric
ton wheat crop will be feed or downgraded quality this season.
The cost of the overall downgrade may approach A$1 billion, with
losses from flooding still unclear at this stage, the bank said
in an e-mailed report today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
